Hespori can easily be tackled with low cost equipment. Use knives, darts, or a powered stave to attack the flowers that hespori spawns at 100%, 66% and 33% health, and use special attacks such as a [[dragon dagger]] where possible to speed up the fight. At lower levels you will encounter Hespori's immobilizing special attack at least once per fight, and it is important to click away repeatedly or risk taking a large amount of damage at once.

Thralls and death charge for the flowers can be used for additional damage and access to an extra special attack or two during the fight. 

===Inventory===
*[[Dragon dagger]] for special attacks
*[[Hespori seed]], [[spade]], and, if the bare-handed planting section of [[Barbarian training]] is incomplete, a [[seed dibber]] to harvest and replant Hespori
*[[Super combat potion]] or a [[super set]]
*[[Knives]] or [[darts]] to quickly kill flowers
*[[Rune pouch]] and [[Book of the dead]] to use [[Thralls]]
*A [[prayer potion]] in case of a long fight, or at lower prayer levels
*Any form of [[antipoison]]
*The rest any cooked food

===Notes===
*If casting a thrall, do so after waking hespori.

